sentences: Jim Noir (born 1982) is the stage name of Alan Peter Roberts, an English singer-songwriter from Davyhulme, Greater Manchester.
He has released five albums to date, 2005's Tower of Love, 2008's self-titled LP Jim Noir, 2012's Jimmy's Show, 2014's Finnish Line, and 2019's A.M. Jazz, as well as a number of EPs.
